'''Hamoudi Messaoudene''' is an Algerian inventor from [[Aures, Algeria|Aures]], wilaya of [[Batna, Algeria|Batna]] in [[Algeria]], which has to his credit several patents for inventions at the national<ref>http://www2.horizons-dz.com/?Le-prix-national-attribue-a-la-NCA</ref> and international level. His latest invention<ref>http://www.mdipi.gov.dz/?Nouvel-article,331</ref> is a machine that revolutionized the field of agriculture. The latter U-shaped, that when placed around the shaft clears the weeds. Operation known under the term mechanical weeding or hoeing. This invention won him the first prize for the best invention in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Messaoudene|first1=Hamoudi|title=L’intelligence au service du développement|url=http://www.depechedekabylie.com/mobile/evenement/132098-lintelligence-au-service-du-developpement.html|accessdate=14 July 2015|agency=La dépêche de Kabylie|issue=11 December 2013|publisher=La dépêche de Kabylie|date=11 December 2013}}</ref> He was a guest on several television channels Algerian, including [[Canal Algérie|Canal Algerie]], where he explains the use of the machine in terms of efficiency and profitability for growers.

